Package org.bluezoo.gumdrop.telemetry.metrics

Class HistogramDataPoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.bluezoo.gumdrop.telemetry.metrics.HistogramDataPoint
  • public final class HistogramDataPoint
extends java.lang.Object
    A single data point for a histogram metric. Contains the distribution of values across explicit buckets.
    Author:
    Chris Burdess

                          double sum,
                          long[] bucketCounts,
                          double[] explicitBounds,
                          double min,
                          double max)
        Creates a histogram data point.
        Parameters:
        attributes - the attributes identifying this time series
        startTimeUnixNano - the start time for cumulative temporality
        timeUnixNano - the timestamp of this data point
        count - the total number of recorded values
        sum - the sum of all recorded values
        bucketCounts - the count of values in each bucket (length = bounds.length + 1)
        explicitBounds - the upper bounds of each bucket (exclusive)
        min - the minimum recorded value
        max - the maximum recorded value

      • getBucketCounts

        public long[] getBucketCounts()
        Returns the count of values in each bucket. The length is explicitBounds.length + 1. Bucket[i] counts values where: bounds[i-1] <= value < bounds[i] The first bucket counts values < bounds[0]. The last bucket counts values >= bounds[length-1].

      • getExplicitBounds
